main event: An unidentified object was observed in the sky in Dickinson, North Dakota on June 19, 1962.
interesting points: The object was tracked by radar and visually observed for 2-3 minutes., It was described as white, round, and high-speed., The object moved in a straight line before disappearing from radar range., There were indications of radar tracking coinciding with visual sightings., The investigation was part of the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book.
